      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Observability and Debugging"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agent runs are harder to debug than chains because the path through the graph changes at runtime. LangSmith traces every step \u2014 tool inputs/outputs, LLM calls, token counts \u2014 and makes the full ReAct trajectory inspectable."
